---
title: Louisiana-Style Bacony Red Beans & Rice with Scallions
description: Our chefs brought classic Louisiana flavors to this Black History Month-inspired play on red beans and rice. You'll simmer hearty red beans with bell pepper, scallions, tomato, cumin, and our Cajun Spice Blend until tender, then pile it all over fluffy white rice and finish with a sprinkle of crispy bacon and scallion greens.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/678565b028c218603675d593-13deff63.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/678565b028c218603675d593-en-US.pdf
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 910 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 114 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 25 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 1750 mg
author: Sara Heilman
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/louisiana-style-bacony-red-beans-and-rice-678565b028c218603675d593
---

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @white rice{3/4%cup} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; toast, stirring frequently, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add 1 1/4 cups water (2 1⁄4 cups for 4 servings); bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Heat a medium dry #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%oz}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer bacon to a #paper towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop. Carefully transfer bacon fat to a #small bowl{} (you'll use it in Step 4). Wipe out pot.

While bacon cooks, wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @green bell pepper{1}(deseeded and diced into 1/4-inch pieces) into 1⁄4-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/4-inch pieces) into 1⁄4-inch pieces.

In pot used for bacon, heat 2 TBSP reserved bacon fat (4 TBSP for 4 servings) over medium heat.

> TIP: If your bacon did not render enough fat, use oil or butter instead.

Slowly whisk in @flour{2%tbsp} and cook, whisking, until no lumps remain and mixture is darkened and bubbling, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Mixture should have a toasty, nutty aroma.

Add bell pepper, scallion whites, @Cajun Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @cumin{1%tsp}, @celery salt{1/2%tsp} (half the celery salt), @sugar{1/4%tsp} (1⁄2 tsp for 4), and @pepper{to taste}. Stir to coat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened and spices are fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1}(stirred in) to pot with veggies and cook, stirring, until combined and slightly darkened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in diced tomato, @kidney beans{1}(with liquid), and 1 cup water (2 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then lower to a simmer and cover. Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Taste beans and season with more @celery salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Divide rice and beans between shallow #bowls{}. Sprinkle with bacon and scallion greens and serve.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.